comments.body:
Is opting out an option during the install now? Personally I would prefer to have to opt in.

@iSazonov environment variables are stored in the in registry so this shouldn't be an issue.

My only concern that users can typically override system environment variables with there user environment variables in controlled enterprises. Only looking for variables value may allow users to override system level policy for telemetry.

@thezim 
> environment variables are stored in the in registry so this shouldn't be an issue.

We can set environment variable by GPP but security men require _forced security policy_.
